Hi, consider the two erroneous statements in the constructor (using TS 0.9 Beta):

```JavaScript
class Foo {
    constructor() {

        // Error TS2094: The property 'foo' does not exist on value of type 'Foo'.
        this.foo();

        // Error TS2158: Untyped function calls may not accept type arguments.
        this.foo<string>();
    }
}
```

Ideally they should both print a TS2094.
